---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import PageHeader from "../components/Sections/PageHeader.astro";
import TeamList from "../components/Sections/TeamList.astro";

const values = [
  {
    heading: "Dignity Before Profit",
    body: "Every member is a person first. BEMA's sponsorship model ensures that charitable care reaches the people who need it without anyone knowing who paid for it and without a single donor dollar touching operational overhead.",
    path: "M12 3l7 4v5c0 4.2-2.6 7.8-7 9-4.4-1.2-7-4.8-7-9V7l7-4z",
  },
  {
    heading: "Radical Transparency",
    body: "Every dollar donated to BEMA goes directly to funding care for someone in need. None of it covers operations, salaries, or administrative costs.",
    path: "M4 12s3-6 8-6 8 6 8 6-3 6-8 6-8-6-8-6zm8 3a3 3 0 100-6 3 3 0 000 6z",
  },
  {
    heading: "Empathy in Action",
    body: "BEMA does not position itself as a savior. It positions itself as a guide that has already done the hard work of figuring out the system so its members do not have to.",
    path: "M12 3l8 18-8-4-8 4 8-18z",
  },
  {
    heading: "Whole-Person Care",
    body: "Because health does not come in separate categories, BEMA coordinates access to Direct Primary Care, Eye Care, and Mental Health services under a single membership so members can address their full picture of health in one place.",
    path: "M7 8a4 4 0 118 0 4 4 0 01-8 0zm-4 12a6 6 0 0112 0M16 14a4 4 0 014 4v2",
  },
];
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About | BEMA - Healthcare Access for Florida's Working Families"
  description="BEMA is a Florida nonprofit coordinating access to Direct Primary Care, Eye Care, and Mental Health services for working families caught in the insurance gap."
>
  <PageHeader
    title="We exist because the current healthcare system left too many people behind."
    subtitle="BEMA is a Florida nonprofit that coordinates access to Direct Primary Care, Eye Care, and Mental Health services for working individuals and families who have fallen through the insurance gap."
    imageSrc="/images/about-story.jpg"
    imageAlt="A diverse group of working adults in a sunny Florida community setting, warm and approachable, not clinical."
  />

  <section class="section-pad bg-bema-white">
    <div class="container">
      <figure class="mx-auto max-w-4xl text-center">
        <blockquote class="font-display text-3xl font-bold leading-tight text-bema-green md:text-5xl">
          BEMA exists so that working families in Florida never have to choose between the care they need and the life they are trying to build.
        </blockquote>
        <figcaption class="mt-6 font-semibold text-bema-khaki">The BEMA Mission</figcaption>
      </figure>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section-pad bg-bema-white">
    <div class="container grid gap-12 lg:grid-cols-2 lg:items-center">
      <div>
        <p class="eyebrow">Our story</p>
        <h2 class="mt-3">Built from the ground up for the people the system forgot.</h2>
        <p class="mt-6 text-lg text-bema-green/85">BEMA was founded by a group of Florida healthcare professionals who saw the same problem repeating itself every day. Working adults coming in for care they had delayed because the cost was too high. Families making choices between a doctor visit and a bill they could not afford. People who were employed, contributing, and doing everything right, and still falling through a gap that the current system was never designed to close.</p>
        <p class="mt-6 text-lg text-bema-green/85">They built BEMA to close it. Not as a clinic, not as an insurance product, but as a coordination organization that sits between the member and the care they need and handles everything in between. BEMA partners with independent clinics already serving Florida communities and coordinates access to Direct Primary Care, Eye Care, and Mental Health services under a single predictable monthly program service fee. The mission is simple. No working family in Florida should have to choose between the care they need and the life they are trying to build.</p>
      </div>
      <img
        src="/images/about-story.jpg"
        alt="[PLACEHOLDER: Alt text for founders or organizational image]"
        class="min-h-80 w-full rounded-lg border border-bema-khaki/40 object-cover"
        loading="lazy"
        decoding="async"
      />
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section-pad bg-bema-khaki-light/20">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="mb-12 max-w-3xl">
        <p class="eyebrow">Core values</p>
        <h2>What we stand for.</h2>
      </div>
      <div class="grid gap-8 md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-4">
        {values.map((value) => (
          <article class="card p-6">
            <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" class="mb-5 h-10 w-10 text-bema-green" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.8" aria-hidden="true">
              <path d={value.path} stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"></path>
            </svg>
            <h3 class="text-2xl">{value.heading}</h3>
            <p class="mt-4 text-bema-green/85">{value.body}</p>
          </article>
        ))}
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section-pad bg-bema-white">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="max-w-4xl">
        <p class="eyebrow">Coordination model</p>
        <h2 class="mt-3">Coordination is the product.</h2>
        <p class="mt-6 text-lg text-bema-green/85">Most healthcare organizations ask you to navigate the system yourself. Find a doctor. Check if they are in network. Submit a claim. Wait. Follow up. BEMA was built on a different premise. The coordination is the product. When you become a member, BEMA takes on the work of connecting you to the right partner clinic, managing the logistics in between, and making sure nothing falls through the cracks.</p>
        <p class="mt-6 text-lg text-bema-green/85">This model exists because the people BEMA serves should not have to become experts in navigating a broken system just to get a primary care visit, an eye exam, or a Mental Health appointment. BEMA handles the complexity so that members can focus on their health and partner clinics can focus entirely on delivering care.</p>
        <div class="mt-8 border-l-4 border-bema-khaki bg-bema-khaki-light/20 p-6 text-lg font-medium text-bema-green">
          BEMA does not deliver medical care directly. BEMA connects members to a network of independent partner clinics. The clinic provides the care. BEMA handles the coordination.
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <TeamList />
</BaseLayout>
